description: Exactly 5 digits from {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9} can precede a(n) to form a lucky number.
comments: Finding 6, 7, 8 and 9 preceding digits is a difficult job !
example: If n = 977 then we find only '1'977, '2'977, '4'977, '5'977 and '8'977 to be lucky numbers.
author: _Patrick De Geest_, May 15 1998
